import pandas as pd

# Convert 'Tweet Posted Time (Utc)' column to datetime format
df['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Tweet Posted Time (Utc)']).dt.year

# Count total tweets for each year
total_tweets_per_year = df['Year'].value_counts().sort_index()

# Filter tweets related to fluoridation
fluoridation_tweets = df[df['Tweet Content'].str.contains('fluoridation', case=False)]

# Count tweets related to fluoridation for each year
fluoridation_tweets_per_year = fluoridation_tweets['Year'].value_counts().sort_index()

# Create a DataFrame to store the comparison
comparison_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'Total Tweets': total_tweets_per_year,
    'Fluoridation Tweets': fluoridation_tweets_per_year
})

# Fill missing years with 0
comparison_df.fillna(0, inplace=True)

# Print the comparison DataFrame
print(comparison_df)

# Filter tweets related to fluoridation
fluoridation_tweets = df[df['Tweet Content'].str.contains('fluoridation', case=False)]

# Group by 'Year'
grouped_by_year = fluoridation_tweets.groupby('Year')

# Initialize lists to store results
years = []
tweets_with_more_than_10_retweets = []
tweets_with_more_than_10_favorites = []

# Iterate over groups
for year, group_data in grouped_by_year:
    # Filter tweets with more than 10 retweets and more than 10 favorites for this year
    tweets_more_than_10_retweets = group_data[group_data['RETWEETS'] > 10]
    tweets_more_than_10_favorites = group_data[group_data['FAVORITES'] > 10]
    
    # Append year and counts to lists
    years.append(year)
    tweets_with_more_than_10_retweets.append(len(tweets_more_than_10_retweets))
    tweets_with_more_than_10_favorites.append(len(tweets_more_than_10_favorites))


# Calculate the width of each bar
bar_width = 0.35

# Plot the comparison for each year
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Position of each bar on x-axis
x = np.arange(len(years))

# Plot bars for tweets with more than 10 retweets
plt.bar(x - bar_width/2, tweets_with_more_than_10_retweets, width=bar_width, color='skyblue', label='Retweets > 10')

# Plot bars for tweets with more than 10 favorites
plt.bar(x + bar_width/2, tweets_with_more_than_10_favorites, width=bar_width, color='salmon', label='Favorites > 10')

# Add labels, title, and legend
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Tweets')
plt.title('Comparison of Tweets Related to Fluoridation')
plt.xticks(x, years)
plt.legend()

# Show plot
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import pandas as pd
from afinn import Afinn

# Load the AFINN lexicon
afinn = Afinn()

# Tokenize tweet content and calculate sentiment score for each tweet
df['Sentiment Score'] = df['Tweet Content'].apply(lambda x: afinn.score(x))

# Classify sentiment as positive, negative, or neutral
df['Sentiment'] = df['Sentiment Score'].apply(lambda score: 'positive' if score > 0 else ('negative' if score < 0 else 'neutral'))

# Display sentiment distribution
sentiment_distribution = df['Sentiment'].value_counts(normalize=True)
print("Sentiment Distribution:")
print(sentiment_distribution)

# Display top positive words
positive_words = df[df['Sentiment'] == 'positive']['Tweet Content'].str.split(expand=True).stack()
positive_word_scores = positive_words.apply(lambda word: afinn.score(word))
positive_word_sentiment = pd.DataFrame({'Word': positive_words, 'Sentiment Score': positive_word_scores})
top_positive_words = positive_word_sentiment.groupby('Word')['Sentiment Score'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
print("\nTop Positive Words:")
print(top_positive_words)

# Display top negative words
negative_words = df[df['Sentiment'] == 'negative']['Tweet Content'].str.split(expand=True).stack()
negative_word_scores = negative_words.apply(lambda word: afinn.score(word))
negative_word_sentiment = pd.DataFrame({'Word': negative_words, 'Sentiment Score': negative_word_scores})
top_negative_words = negative_word_sentiment.groupby('Word')['Sentiment Score'].mean().sort_values().head(10)
print("\nTop Negative Words:")
print(top_negative_words)

# Display top neutral words
neutral_words = df[df['Sentiment'] == 'neutral']['Tweet Content'].str.split(expand=True).stack()
neutral_word_scores = neutral_words.apply(lambda word: afinn.score(word))
neutral_word_sentiment = pd.DataFrame({'Word': neutral_words, 'Sentiment Score': neutral_word_scores})
top_neutral_words = neutral_word_sentiment.groupby('Word')['Sentiment Score'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
print("\nTop Neutral Words:")
print(top_neutral_words)

import pandas as pd
from afinn import Afinn

# Load the AFINN lexicon
afinn = Afinn()

# Tokenize tweet content and calculate sentiment score for each word
df['Words'] = df['Tweet Content'].str.split()
df['Sentiment Score'] = df['Words'].apply(lambda words: [afinn.score(word) for word in words])

# Create an empty list to store word-level sentiment scores
word_sentiment_data = []

# Iterate through each row to extract words and their sentiment scores
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    words = row['Words']
    scores = row['Sentiment Score']
    for word, score in zip(words, scores):
        sentiment = 'positive' if score > 0 else ('negative' if score < 0 else 'neutral')
        word_sentiment_data.append({'Word': word, 'Sentiment Score': score, 'Sentiment': sentiment})

# Create DataFrame from word-level sentiment scores
word_sentiment_df = pd.DataFrame(word_sentiment_data)

# Group words by sentiment
grouped_words = word_sentiment_df.groupby('Sentiment')

# Create DataFrames for positive, negative, and neutral words
positive_words_df = grouped_words.get_group('positive')
negative_words_df = grouped_words.get_group('negative')
neutral_words_df = grouped_words.get_group('neutral')

# Print DataFrames
print("Positive Words:")
print(positive_words_df.head())
print("\nNegative Words:")
print(negative_words_df.head())
print("\nNeutral Words:")
print(neutral_words_df.head())

# Import necessary libraries
import pandas as pd
import nltk
import re
from afinn import Afinn

# Download NLTK stopwords
nltk.download('stopwords')

# Load the AFINN lexicon
afinn = Afinn()

# Tokenize tweet content and calculate sentiment score for each word
df['Words'] = df['Tweet Content'].str.split()

# Remove stopwords, URLs, and links
stopwords = nltk.corpus.stopwords.words('english')
words_to_exclude = ['47', 'httptcojNNhPCCXG']  # Add words to exclude here
def preprocess_text(words):
    processed_words = []
    for word in words:
        # Remove '#' and normalize 'anti-#vaccine' to 'anti vaccine'
        word = word.replace('#', '')
        word = re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z]', '', word)  # Remove non-alphabetic characters
        if word.lower() not in stopwords and not re.match(r'^https?:\/\/.*[\r\n]*', word) and word not in words_to_exclude:
            processed_words.append(word)
    return processed_words

df['Words'] = df['Words'].apply(preprocess_text)

# Calculate sentiment score for each word
df['Sentiment Score'] = df['Words'].apply(lambda words: [afinn.score(word) for word in words])

# Create an empty list to store word-level sentiment scores
word_sentiment_data = []

# Iterate through each row to extract words and their sentiment scores
for index, row in df.iterrows():
    words = row['Words']
    scores = row['Sentiment Score']
    for word, score in zip(words, scores):
        sentiment = 'positive' if score > 0 else ('negative' if score < 0 else 'neutral')
        word_sentiment_data.append({'Word': word, 'Sentiment Score': score, 'Sentiment': sentiment})

# Create DataFrame from word-level sentiment scores
word_sentiment_df = pd.DataFrame(word_sentiment_data)

# Group words by sentiment
grouped_words = word_sentiment_df.groupby('Sentiment')

# Create DataFrames for positive, negative, and neutral words
positive_words_df = grouped_words.get_group('positive')
negative_words_df = grouped_words.get_group('negative')
neutral_words_df = grouped_words.get_group('neutral')

# Add a new column with normalized frequency for each sentiment category
positive_word_count = positive_words_df['Word'].count()
negative_word_count = negative_words_df['Word'].count()
neutral_word_count = neutral_words_df['Word'].count()

positive_words_df['Normalized Frequency'] = positive_words_df.groupby('Word')['Word'].transform('count') / positive_word_count
negative_words_df['Normalized Frequency'] = negative_words_df.groupby('Word')['Word'].transform('count') / negative_word_count
neutral_words_df['Normalized Frequency'] = neutral_words_df.groupby('Word')['Word'].transform('count') / neutral_word_count

# Drop rows containing the word '47'
positive_words_df = positive_words_df[~positive_words_df['Word'].str.contains('47', case=False)]
negative_words_df = negative_words_df[~negative_words_df['Word'].str.contains('47', case=False)]
neutral_words_df = neutral_words_df[~neutral_words_df['Word'].str.contains('47', case=False)]
neutral_words_df = neutral_words_df[~neutral_words_df['Word'].str.contains('httptcojNNhPCCXG', case=False)]


# Print DataFrames
print("Positive Words:")
print(positive_words_df.head())
print("\nNegative Words:")
print(negative_words_df.head())
print("\nNeutral Words:")
print(neutral_words_df.head())
